<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Baron de Fava</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-30"><hi rend="italic">September 30,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your inference is correct. Both reports of Marquis Romano and Governor
                            Foster are lacking in fullness on points which the Department feels it
                            should ascertain before further discussion, and to that end is about to
                            make independent examination by a trustworthy agent whose instructions
                            are now being prepared.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>